<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,690,1290]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,799,823]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Remarks</emphasis>
. Material examined here came from a station on the inner continental shelf off Vero Beach. With the exception of its occurrence on floating 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fraser 1944)" baseAuthorityName="Fraser" baseAuthorityYear="1944" box="[596,881,834,859]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Sargassaceae" genus="Sargassum" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fucales" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[596,718,835,859]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Sargassum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fraser, C. M." box="[734,873,834,858]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" refId="ref52677" refString="Fraser, C. M. (1944) Hydroids of the Atlantic coast of North America. University of Toronto Press, Toronto, 451 pp." type="book" year="1944">Fraser 1944</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Nutting, 1900" authorityName="Nutting" authorityYear="1900" box="[894,1299,834,859]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Plumulariidae" genus="Plumularia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="floridana">
<emphasis box="[894,1134,835,859]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Plumularia floridana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Nutting, C. C." box="[1143,1299,834,858]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="1 - 285" refId="ref57545" refString="Nutting, C. C. (1900) American hydroids. Part I. The Plumularidae. Smithsonian Institution, United States National Museum Special Bulletin, 4 (1), 1 - 285." type="journal article" year="1900">Nutting, 1900</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is a species more frequently recorded inshore than offshore along the southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[939,1091,870,894]" name="United States of America" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">United States</collectingCountry>
. While common in estuaries of 
<collectingRegion box="[151,321,906,930]" country="United States of America" name="South Carolina" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">South Carolina</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Calder, D. R. &amp; Hester, B. S." box="[337,593,906,930]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="87 - 93" refId="ref50072" refString="Calder, D. R. &amp; Hester, B. S. (1978) Phylum Cnidaria. In: Zingmark, R. G. (Ed.), An annotated checklist of the biota of the coastal zone of South Carolina. University of South Carolina Press, Columbia, pp. 87 - 93." type="book chapter" year="1978">Calder &amp; Hester 1978</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Calder, D. R." box="[606,748,906,930]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="7 - 28" refId="ref49281" refString="Calder, D. R. (1983) Hydroida from estuaries of South Carolina, USA: families Sertulariidae and Plumulariidae. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 96, 7 - 28." type="journal article" year="1983">Calder 1983</bibRefCitation>
), it has not yet been reported from hard bottom areas on the shelf between 
<collectingRegion box="[318,489,942,966]" country="United States of America" name="North Carolina" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">North Carolina</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[550,630,942,966]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Florida</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cain, T. D." box="[648,771,942,966]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="79 - 82" refId="ref49064" refString="Cain, T. D. (1972) Additional epifauna of a reef off North Carolina. Journal of the Elisha Mitchell Scientific Society, 88, 79 - 82." type="journal article" year="1972">Cain 1972</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Wenner, E. L. &amp; Hinde, P. &amp; Knott, D. M. &amp; Van Dolah, R. F." box="[785,1010,942,966]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" refId="ref62103" refString="Wenner, E. L., Hinde, P., Knott, D. M. &amp; Van Dolah, R. F. (1984) A temporal and spatial study of invertebrate communities associated with hard-bottom habitats in the South Atlantic Bight. United States Department of Commerce, National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration, National Marine Fisheries Service, NOAA Technical Report NMFS, 18, 104 pp." type="book" year="1984">
Wenner 
<emphasis box="[881,933,942,966]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">et al</emphasis>
. 1984
</bibRefCitation>
). As noted earlier (
<bibRefCitation author="Calder, D. R." box="[1234,1379,942,966]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="1 - 85" refId="ref49769" refString="Calder, D. R. (1997) Shallow-water hydroids of Bermuda: superfamily Plumularioidea. Royal Ontario Museum, Life Sciences Contributions, 161, 1 - 85." type="journal article" year="1997">Calder 1997</bibRefCitation>
), the species is eurytopic, surviving temperatures down to 10° C and salinities as low as 25‰.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,690,1290]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
An extensive synonymy of this species is listed in 
<bibRefCitation author="Ansin Agis, J. &amp; Ramil, F. &amp; Vervoort, W." box="[775,1054,1014,1038]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="1 - 268" refId="ref47406" refString="Ansin Agis, J., Ramil, F. &amp; Vervoort, W. (2001) Atlantic Leptolida (Hydrozoa, Cnidaria) of the families Aglaopheniidae, Halopterididae, Kirchenpaueriidae and Plumulariidae collected during the CANCAP and Mauritania-II expeditions of the National Museum of Natural History, Leiden, the Netherlands. Zoologische Verhandelingen, 333, 1 - 268." type="journal article" year="2001">
Ansín Agís 
<emphasis box="[912,962,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">et al</emphasis>
. (2001)
</bibRefCitation>
, who described material from the Canary Islands.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,690,1290]" box="[199,1073,1086,1111]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,466,1086,1111]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Reported distribution.</emphasis>
Atlantic coast of 
<collectingRegion box="[665,750,1086,1110]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Florida</collectingRegion>
. Biscayne 
<collectingRegion box="[870,915,1087,1111]" country="Cayman Islands" name="West Bay" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Bay</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Jones, T." box="[930,1062,1086,1110]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" refId="ref54656" refString="Jones, T. (2002) Biology and ecology of athecate hydroids in Biscayne Bay, Florida: potential use as bioindicators. Ph. D. Dissertation, University of Miami, Coral Gables, 287 pp." type="book" year="2002">Jones 2002</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,690,1290]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Western Atlantic. South Carolina (
<bibRefCitation author="Calder, D. R." box="[605,751,1122,1146]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="7 - 28" refId="ref49281" refString="Calder, D. R. (1983) Hydroida from estuaries of South Carolina, USA: families Sertulariidae and Plumulariidae. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 96, 7 - 28." type="journal article" year="1983">Calder 1983</bibRefCitation>
) to 
<collectingCountry box="[806,874,1122,1146]" name="Brazil" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(Oliveira 
<emphasis box="[1001,1056,1123,1147]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">et al</emphasis>
. submitted), including 
<collectingCountry box="[1333,1436,1122,1146]" name="Bermuda" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Bermuda</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Calder, D. R." box="[158,305,1158,1182]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="1 - 85" refId="ref49769" refString="Calder, D. R. (1997) Shallow-water hydroids of Bermuda: superfamily Plumularioidea. Royal Ontario Museum, Life Sciences Contributions, 161, 1 - 85." type="journal article" year="1997">Calder 1997</bibRefCitation>
) and the Gulf of Mexico (
<bibRefCitation author="Calder, D. R. &amp; Cairns, S. D." box="[635,907,1158,1182]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" refId="ref49991" refString="Calder, D. R. &amp; Cairns, S. D. (2009) Hydroids (Cnidaria: Hydrozoa) of the Gulf of Mexico. In: Felder, D. L. &amp; Camp, D. K. (Eds.), Gulf of Mexico. Origin, waters, and biota. Vol. 1. Biodiversity. Texas A &amp; M University Press, College Station, pp. 381 - 394." type="book" year="2009">Calder &amp; Cairns 2009</bibRefCitation>
). It extends northwards to New 
<collectingCountry box="[1302,1395,1158,1182]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">England</collectingCountry>
on 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fraser 1944)" baseAuthorityName="Fraser" baseAuthorityYear="1944" box="[151,434,1194,1219]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Sargassaceae" genus="Sargassum" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fucales" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,273,1195,1219]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Sargassum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fraser, C. M." box="[287,426,1194,1218]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" refId="ref52677" refString="Fraser, C. M. (1944) Hydroids of the Atlantic coast of North America. University of Toronto Press, Toronto, 451 pp." type="book" year="1944">Fraser 1944</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,690,1290]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Elsewhere. Believed to be circumglobal, mostly in tropical and warm-temperate waters (
<bibRefCitation author="Ansin Agis, J. &amp; Ramil, F. &amp; Vervoort, W." pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="1 - 268" refId="ref47406" refString="Ansin Agis, J., Ramil, F. &amp; Vervoort, W. (2001) Atlantic Leptolida (Hydrozoa, Cnidaria) of the families Aglaopheniidae, Halopterididae, Kirchenpaueriidae and Plumulariidae collected during the CANCAP and Mauritania-II expeditions of the National Museum of Natural History, Leiden, the Netherlands. Zoologische Verhandelingen, 333, 1 - 268." type="journal article" year="2001">
Ansín Agís 
<emphasis box="[1376,1429,1230,1254]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">et al</emphasis>
. 2001
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
